.TH kopt 8
.SH NAME
.PP
\*Lkopt\*O \- Selects various kernel options.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.iX "kopt command"
.iX "kernel" "selecting options with kopt"
.sS
\*L/usr/sbin/kopt\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The \*Lkopt\*O command allows users to select among various kernel options.
When you invoke the command, a list of kernel options appears along with
a prompt for you to specify the options you want.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
The following example selects all four kernel options.
.iS
# /usr/sbin/kopt

*** KERNEL OPTION SELECTION ***

    Selection   Kernel Option
---------------------------------------------------------------
        1       Reserve Kernel Debug Space
        2       Streams Socket Coexistence (DLPI & STRIFNET)
        3       X/Open Transport Interface (XTISO)
        4       ISO 9660 Compact Disc File System (CDFS)
        5       All of the above
        6       None of the above
---------------------------------------------------------------

Enter the selection number for each kernel option you want.
For example, 1 3 : 5
.iE
.EQ
delim off
.EN
